---
alwaysApply: true
---

# Control flow

- Early returns over if/else nesting
- No goto, recursion, complex flow

# Loops

- Fixed upper bounds required

# Functions

- Small (~60 lines max)
- Single purpose
- Pure functions, no side effects!

# Defensive Coding

- Use assertions
- Check returns
- Validate inputs

# Scope

- Smallest possible variable scope
- No globals or variable reuse

# Quality

- Zero warnings
- Fix analyzer issues
- Fewer lines better

# Style

- NO Classes! Use a functional approach as much as possible!
- No semicolons
- Single quotes for JSX/HTML
- Blank line at file end
- TypeScript with types
- Destructure props >2 keys.
- Prefer one prop object over 2+ individual params for functions.
- Keep existing comments.
- Add ONLY WHY comments - if something is not obvious
- Do NOT add WHAT comments - simple descriptions
- Keep function calls clean - build and define props upfront
- Path aliases: `@server/`, `@shared/`, `@/*`... (for all within src) -> follow tsconfig

# Problem Solving

- Analyze first
- Consider alternatives
- Focus on relevant
- No overengineering

# Architecture: Reusable Business Logic

- Business logic = pure functions with NO framework knowledge
- All dependencies (DB, services) injected as function parameters
- Same function callable from HTTP routes, background jobs, and tests
- Unit of Work pattern: each operation is self-contained and testable
- Test ONLY the business commands, not infrastructure
- Example: `enrichProfile({ id, data, persistenceProvider, serviceProvider })`

# CSS and Styling

- Use Tailwind classes, Flex and Grid
- Use ShadCN components from the components/ui folder
- Use flex + gap. DO NOT Use space-x-[value] or space-y-[]
- Prefer layout position and spacing from the parent to the children, over margin
